      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If your app uses this method to pause recording, such as when the user taps the pause button in a game, you can resume later with another call to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.classkit/documentation/ClassKit/CLSActivity/start()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " on the same activity when the user resumes the task associated with the activity. But if the user makes a new attempt at the task, for example by starting a game level over, and your app creates a new activity with a call to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.classkit/documentation/ClassKit/CLSContext/createNewActivity()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", then the framework stops the old one permanently and makes it inaccessible to your app thereafter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
